# Section Keywords start BLOCKS.  They are:
# 
# | Keyword        | What it defines                              | Analogy                                  |
# | -------------- | -------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
# | IMAPAccount    | "Connection credentials (Host/User/Pass)."   | The Who: Your ID card.                   |
# | IMAPStore      | A remote server storage area.                | The Where (Far): The cloud.              |
# | MaildirStore   | A local folder storage area.                 | The Where (Near): Your hard drive.       |
# | Channel        | The link between a Far and Near store.       | The Bridge: The path between them.       |
# | Group          | A collection of Channels.                    | The Batch: A list of bridges to cross.   |

## YAHOO
IMAPAccount yahoo
    Host imap.mail.yahoo.com
    User goobsoft@yahoo.com
    # Use your 16-character App Password here
    Pass "hcavhihpgrnpqlid"
    TLSType IMAPS
    # Port 993 is the default for IMAPS
    AuthMechs LOGIN
    # Concurrent Fetching
    PipelineDepth 15

IMAPStore yahoo-remote
    Account yahoo

MaildirStore yahoo-local
    # The trailing slash is important for Maildir
    Path ~/.mail/yahoo/
    Inbox ~/.mail/yahoo/Inbox
    SubFolders Verbatim
    # This keeps folder names simple (e.g., ~/.mail/yahoo/Sent)
    Flatten .

Channel yahoo
    Far :yahoo-remote:
    Near :yahoo-local:
    # Sync all folders
    Patterns * !.*
    # Automatically create local folders if they exist on the server
    Create Near
    # Automatically delete local copies if deleted on the server
    Sync All
    Expunge Near
    Expunge Far
    # Store sync state in a file to make subsequent syncs faster
    SyncState *

## RCC (Outlook)
IMAPAccount rcc
    Host outlook.office365.com
    Port 993
    User chad.skeeters@redcedarconsultancy.com
    # Pass ""
    PassCmd "op_password 5cptk7fi2da7pnck2qkkxxv22m"
    # PassSecret your-password
    TLSType IMAPS
    # Port 993 is the default for IMAPS
    AuthMechs LOGIN
    # Concurrent Fetching
    PipelineDepth 15

IMAPStore rcc-remote
    Account rcc

MaildirStore rcc-local
    # The trailing slash is important for Maildir
    Path ~/.mail/rcc/
    Inbox ~/.mail/rcc/Inbox
    SubFolders Verbatim
    # This keeps folder names simple (e.g., ~/.mail/yahoo/Sent)
    Flatten .

Channel rcc
    Far :rcc-remote:
    Near :rcc-local:
    # For testing, only sync last 30 days
    MaxMessages 30
    # Sync all folders
    Patterns * !.*
    # Automatically create local folders if they exist on the server
    Create Near
    # Automatically delete local copies if deleted on the server
    Sync All
    Expunge Near
    Expunge Far
    # Store sync state in a file to make subsequent syncs faster
    SyncState *

## Helpers

Group all
    Channel yahoo
    Channel rcc
